{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":21096,"record_hash":"sha256:2b1d570b89d4491f9db12458e8f6411479745e203af0efa1f36af68f5295939b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T20:36:24.501Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"My recommendation: **keep the stored data shape as-is, but add small read-side GitMeta APIs before building any consumer.**\n\nThe current agentlog shape is good for the two future use cases:\n\n- Project-scoped durable sessions work for handoff before any code exists.\n- Future branch/PR/change targets can point to sessions without owning transcript data.\n- One session can relate to many PRs/branches, and one PR/branch can relate to many sessions.\n- Transcript records contain enough normalized fields for browsing and enough redacted `source_record` for future provider-specific reconstruction.\n\nI would not change that yet.\n\nWhat I would change is GitMeta ergonomics. We added `set_record`, which made writing sane. Reading should get the same treatment, otherwise the first handoff/review reader will be full of manual `get_value`, `MetaValue` matching, prefix stripping, and JSON parsing.\n\nI’d add these to GitMeta:\n\n```rust\nhandle.get_record<T>(prefix) -> Result<Option<T>>\nhandle.set_members(key) -> Result<BTreeSet<String>>\nhandle.list_json_entries<T>(key) -> Result<Vec<ListJsonEntry<T>>>\n```\n\nThen, in `but-agentlog`, later add a tiny reader API like:\n\n```rust\nlist_sessions(repo, target) -> Vec<AgentSessionSummary>\nget_session(repo, target, session_key) -> AgentSession\n```\n\nI would **not** build the agentlog reader yet unless we need it for tests or a command. But I would add the GitMeta primitives soon, because they are generic, small, and directly unlock both future access patterns.\n\nSo the order I’d choose:\n\n1. Add GitMeta read-side helpers.\n2. Keep current agentlog storage unchanged.\n3. Maybe add tests proving the current written data can be read back through those helpers.\n4. Defer agentlog-specific reader/domain APIs until we have an actual consumer.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T20:36:24.501Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}